         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/9/79 ¶  ¶ This day, dear Mr Buchanan, ¶  I had a visit from Capt Rowan, ¶  who incidentally told me, that you had issued a volume of lithograms of N. Z. grasses. ¶  If so, would you spare me kindly...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.09.18b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A644, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/9/79</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This day, dear Mr Buchanan,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">John Buchanan (1819-1898).</p>
               </note> I had a visit from Capt Rowan,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Presumably F. C. Rowan.</p>
               </note> who incidentally told me, that you had issued a volume of lithograms of N. Z. grasses.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Buchanan (1880). This work is a reissue of a folio size nature-printed edition, produced from photolithography of the original plates and printed at half natural size (p. iv). The full-size plates were issued from December 1877 (p. iii). M was sent a copy: see M to J. Hector, 9 April 1880.</p>
               </note> If so, would you spare me kindly a copy? Tell me, what you <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">have</hi>
               </seg> of my works, so that I can send you any available yet, wanting there. Did you do anything with the <name key="Carex">Carex</name>, which Prof Kirk<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Thomas Kirk.</p>
               </note> thought graminous.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Can Prof Kirk, to whom I wish to be kindly remembered, not give any information on the Water-plant of your Rivers with flowers like <name key="Hydropeltis%20peltata">Hydropeltis peltata</name>,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Not in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">IPNI</seg>, but the name is used in <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Linnaea</seg> (1840), vol. 14, p. 194, in note 6 on recent literature.</p>
               </note> so that good specimens might be obtained in flower &amp; <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ripe</hi>
               </seg> fruit &amp; leaves</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Carex">Carex</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hydropeltis%20peltata">Hydropeltis peltata</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
